After creating all files, run these commands:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-c13dd1ffc9354ee398a3808be4c0330d/VetClinic
# Delete existing migration and database
rm -rf Data/Migrations Data/app.db
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
dotnet ef database update
```

### 11. Modify Program.cs

Add this line BEFORE `app.Run();` to auto-apply migrations on startup:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
}
```

Also disable the RequireConfirmedAccount to make local dev easier:
Change `options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = true;` to `options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = false;`

### 12. Build and verify

```bash
cd /tmp/sv-c13dd1ffc9354ee398a3808be4c0330d/VetClinic
dotnet build
